cs.IR, cs.LG, cs.CL, cs.CV, cs.AI 

This paper is about training fast matching models in Search Ads, which involves information retrieval (IR) and natural language processing (NLP) techniques. Therefore, cs.IR and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a novel training scheme that involves learning from weakly annotated data, which is related to machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL) techniques. Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the proposed framework involves image processing techniques for scoring the unlabeled data, which is related to computer vision (CV) techniques. Therefore, cs.CV is also a possible sub-category.
